article.headline: New Hampshire 78, Vermont 57
article.story: DURHAM, N.H. (AP) --Marcus Bullock scored 20 points to lead New Hampshire to a 78-57 win over Vermont on Saturday. New Hampshire (8-18, 4-12 America East) took an early 13-4 lead but back-to-back three-pointers by Alex Jensen and Corey Sullivan brought Vermont within 3 with 12:44 left in the first half. New Hampshire answered with a 12-2 run fueled by lay-ups by Jermaine Anderson and Bullock, followed by a 13-8 run that made the score 38-20 at halftime. Vermont (17-7, 13-2 America East) cut the lead to 44-27 in the second before it received a bench technical foul. Bullock converted both free-throws followed by a long three-pointer. Damione Liddell connected on a layup on the next possession giving UNH its largest lead of the day at 51-27 with 16:01 to play. Vermont could not cut the lead below 16 points in the remainder of the second half. Anderson had 13 points, four assists and two steals for New Hampshire. Sullivan scored a team-high 13 points for Vermont.
